1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:09,093 --> 00:00:12,826
I slept with your friend behind your back. I lied to you over and over.

3
00:00:12,917 --> 00:00:15,062
I love you, Dao, but back then it just—

4
00:00:15,102 --> 00:00:17,669
Don’t say you love me. That’s disgusting.

5
00:00:19,380 --> 00:00:21,810
Thanks for helping out.

6
00:00:24,509 --> 00:00:26,379
Are you sure it’s okay for me to draw these?

7
00:00:26,764 --> 00:00:30,980
I figured if someone finished them, my mom would be happy.

8
00:00:31,226 --> 00:00:32,942
She’s not in pain anymore.

9
00:00:33,229 --> 00:00:36,339
She’s just… not here anymore.

10
00:00:47,340 --> 00:00:47,980
Direk.

11
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:50,750
What?

12
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,430
Are you immortal or something?

13
00:00:59,514 --> 00:01:00,912
What the hell kind of question is that?

14
00:01:04,414 --> 00:01:05,958
Are you going to die before me?

15
00:01:10,071 --> 00:01:11,450
Can you wait until I die first?

16
00:01:15,853 --> 00:01:17,020
Are you crazy?

17
00:01:17,140 --> 00:01:19,790
Of course I’ll die first. I’m way older than you.

18
00:01:25,642 --> 00:01:27,530
I’m not dying that easily.

19
00:01:29,450 --> 00:01:30,510
You never know, Direk.

20
00:01:36,810 --> 00:01:37,730
Damn it.

21
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:40,300
I really hate this, Direk.

22
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:47,050
Alright then.

23
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:48,940
I’ll let you die first.

24
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:52,240
If I end up dying, I’ll have someone take you out before me.

25
00:01:52,970 --> 00:01:53,710
Okay?

26
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:57,820
Sure.

27
00:02:08,562 --> 00:02:09,671
Let me ask you something.

28
00:02:10,850 --> 00:02:12,990
Don’t you ever think about opening your heart to someone?

29
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,180
If I really die someday,

30
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:17,730
you’ll have no one left.

31
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:22,940
No.

32
00:02:23,940 --> 00:02:25,340
I don’t want to get attached to anyone.

33
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:29,690
Honey,

34
00:02:29,980 --> 00:02:32,220
our son doesn’t believe in love at all.

35
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:35,940
Do you think it’s because of us?

36
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:38,170
When you left,

37
00:02:38,340 --> 00:02:39,910
I almost died too.

38
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:43,160
Is that why

39
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,450
he doesn’t want to fall in love?

40
00:02:47,940 --> 00:02:51,560
Will I ever get to see him love someone before I die?

41
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:36,500
Hey.

42
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:39,470
Don’t tell anyone about what happened yesterday.

43
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:41,020
Especially that asshole North.

44
00:04:42,850 --> 00:04:44,060
Why would I tell him?

45
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,250
Well…

46
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:48,530
In case he makes fun of me.

47
00:04:49,228 --> 00:04:50,299
Why would he?

48
00:04:50,850 --> 00:04:52,210
It’s not even funny.

49
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:55,600
Idiot.

50
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:56,940
Hey.

51
00:04:57,170 --> 00:04:59,450
Maybe you should ask yourself what you find funny.

52
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:04,900
Anyway,

53
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,840
thanks.

54
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,280
For helping me.

55
00:05:10,290 --> 00:05:10,950
Yeah.

56
00:05:39,466 --> 00:05:40,881
You're really gone, Emma.

57
00:05:44,885 --> 00:05:45,731
I used to think

58
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,140
that if you were really gone,

59
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,780
I’d be able to handle it.

60
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:55,610
But it’s not that easy.

61
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:02,970
If you believe I’m strong enough to move on,

62
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:06,930
then I’ll do it.

63
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:32,140
How did you know my mom was gone?

64
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:36,840
I don’t know.

65
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,570
Just a feeling.

66
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,400
That she’s in a better place now.

67
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:47,250
A better place?

68
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,450
Like where?

69
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,490
I don’t know.

70
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:54,300
I just know she’s somewhere better.

71
00:06:55,050 --> 00:06:56,580
After that, I don’t know.

72
00:06:57,730 --> 00:07:00,440
If you say she’s in a better place, does that mean she really is?

73
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:04,660
You’re wondering if she’s happy right now?

74
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:06,360
Yeah.

75
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,940
Do you think that’s true?

76
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:12,020
I don’t know.

77
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:12,940
What?

78
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:14,670
Damn.

79
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:16,890
You’re supposed to comfort me.

80
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:19,920
Like, “Your mom’s definitely happy,” or something.

81
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:25,240
I honestly don’t know if your mom is happy.

82
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,090
But what I do know is—

83
00:07:29,260 --> 00:07:30,010
What?

84
00:07:31,260 --> 00:07:32,580
Your mom

85
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,000
wants you to be very happy.

86
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:46,410
No matter what, she’s not here anymore.

87
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,670
The one who’s still alive

88
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:53,320
deserves to be the happiest.

89
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,120
If you keep being this sad,

90
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,990
how can your mom be happy?

91
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:08,220
So,

92
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:12,240
from now on, live as happily as you can.

93
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:19,680
You know what?

94
00:08:22,130 --> 00:08:24,360
No one’s ever told me that before.

95
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:33,050
That’s because you’ve never shown anyone you’re hurting.

96
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,130
Who’s hurting?

97
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,500
Shut up, idiot.

98
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,560
Hey.

99
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:26,050
Hey, what’s wrong?

100
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:26,920
Hey.

101
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:28,780
Wake up.

102
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:30,180
Hey.

103
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:34,620
Hey.

104
00:09:35,930 --> 00:09:36,570
Hey!

105
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:53,830
Hey.

106
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:55,860
You okay?

107
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:03,850
Why did you suddenly pass out?

108
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,900
There were a lot of spirits at the cemetery.

109
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:10,970
And I’ve been using my powers a lot lately.

110
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:14,920
So?

111
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,360
Is there any guarantee

112
00:10:17,490 --> 00:10:19,260
that you’ll be safe every time?

113
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:22,310
What if a ghost wants to hurt you?

114
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:26,340
What if one of those ghosts at the cemetery tried to hurt you? What would happen?

115
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:32,220
I could even die.

116
00:10:32,710 --> 00:10:34,050
Shit.

117
00:10:36,610 --> 00:10:37,190
Hey.

118
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:38,370
I’m sorry.

119
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,290
I shouldn’t have taken you to the cemetery.

120
00:10:42,590 --> 00:10:43,690
It’s okay.

121
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:47,020
I wanted to go anyway.

122
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:51,490
And I don’t really want you to be alone lately.

123
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,600
I don’t get it.

124
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:03,330
Huh?

125
00:11:05,110 --> 00:11:06,500
I don’t get it.

126
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,670
Why do you push yourself this hard?

127
00:11:12,570 --> 00:11:13,700
It’s normal.

128
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:16,870
When I’m sick,

129
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:18,440
my spirit gets weaker.

130
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,830
I’ve had worse.

131
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:24,290
Besides,

132
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,270
Besides what?

133
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,980
I wanted to help as much as I could.

134
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,270
Well,

135
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,500
are you going back to sleep?

136
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,500
Let’s go home.

137
00:11:48,540 --> 00:11:50,960
There are too many spirits here.

138
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:54,270
Yeah.

139
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:02,150
I saw it fall at the cemetery.

140
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:42,760
You’re seriously

141
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:44,810
so nice.

142
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,440
How are you feeling?

143
00:13:16,810 --> 00:13:17,750
Better?

144
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:20,600
Yeah, a bit better.

145
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,670
You draw really well.

146
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:31,230
Just like my mom.

147
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:35,880
I saw your mom’s drawings.

148
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,570
So I tried copying them.

149
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,670
You’re good.

150
00:13:45,310 --> 00:13:46,850
Is there anything you can’t do?

151
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:10,990
Why are you listening to this song?

152
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,410
No reason.

153
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:13,880
Huh?

154
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,470
I didn’t think about it.

155
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:19,440
It was at the top, so I played it.

156
00:14:22,010 --> 00:14:22,620
Damn.

157
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,590
Should I be happy

158
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,970
that you listened to my song for that reason?

159
00:14:29,390 --> 00:14:30,510
Your song?

160
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:31,580
Yeah.

161
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,020
I made it with friends in high school.

162
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:38,210
High school?

163
00:14:39,260 --> 00:14:40,810
You made something like that back then?

164
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:42,870
Cool, right?

165
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,780
Why’d you stop?

166
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,980
We all went our separate ways.

167
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:56,130
As for me,

168
00:14:56,230 --> 00:14:57,580
I just do it for fun sometimes.

169
00:14:58,490 --> 00:15:00,160
But not much lately.

170
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:04,800
That’s a shame.

171
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,080
Why?

172
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:09,660
It’s a good song.

173
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:17,600
Are you hungry?

174
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,090
Yeah, I’m hungry.

175
00:15:22,090 --> 00:15:23,420
Can you cook?

176
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,910
Give it a try.

177
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,310
There’s fresh food in the fridge.

178
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:30,800
The housekeeper stocked it.

179
00:15:35,790 --> 00:15:37,360
Now I believe you can’t cook.

180
00:15:39,737 --> 00:15:40,813
Is there any jam?

181
00:15:41,521 --> 00:15:42,220
Yeah.

182
00:15:42,958 --> 00:15:43,939
In the fridge.

183
00:15:59,702 --> 00:16:01,554
I thought you could do everything.

184
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:05,380
Do you play music?

185
00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:07,244
A little.

186
00:16:08,542 --> 00:16:09,275
What do you play?

187
00:16:10,598 --> 00:16:11,801
Guitar and keyboard.

188
00:16:14,269 --> 00:16:15,164
Come play with me.

189
00:16:15,671 --> 00:16:16,154
Hmm?

190
00:16:17,619 --> 00:16:19,176
I’ve got a music room at my place.

191
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:20,862
Wanna play together?

192
00:16:47,136 --> 00:16:47,933
What are you looking at?

193
00:16:50,201 --> 00:16:50,957
That was cool.

194
00:16:52,109 --> 00:16:52,608
Huh?

195
00:16:53,377 --> 00:16:54,754
What you just played.

196
00:16:55,397 --> 00:16:56,191
It was cool.

197
00:16:56,761 --> 00:16:57,847
You’re really good.

198
00:17:01,903 --> 00:17:03,198
You’re good at guitar too.

199
00:17:04,194 --> 00:17:05,165
Teach me.

200
00:17:06,330 --> 00:17:06,952
Drums, you mean?

201
00:17:07,705 --> 00:17:08,164
Yeah.

202
00:17:10,511 --> 00:17:11,685
What made you want to play?

203
00:17:12,177 --> 00:17:13,348
It looks fun.

204
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:15,334
Come on.

205
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:35,804
How do I hold it?

206
00:17:36,811 --> 00:17:37,469
Just try.

207
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:48,429
Wait, wait.

208
00:17:50,755 --> 00:17:52,678
If you hold it like that, you’ll drop it.

209
00:17:53,251 --> 00:17:54,263
I don’t know how.

210
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:01,114
Hold it like this.

211
00:18:02,355 --> 00:18:03,274
Move your hand up.

212
00:18:04,887 --> 00:18:05,945
Loosen your grip.

213
00:18:07,571 --> 00:18:09,189
Lock it with your thumb.

214
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:10,994
Mm-hmm.

215
00:18:11,337 --> 00:18:12,680
Then hit it slowly.

216
00:18:14,085 --> 00:18:14,668
Okay.

217
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:21,411
Hey!

218
00:18:43,401 --> 00:18:44,371
Sorry.

219
00:18:44,757 --> 00:18:46,034
I zoned out.

220
00:18:52,028 --> 00:18:53,392
Hello, Fah. What’s up?

221
00:18:54,637 --> 00:18:55,856
Hey, go ahead and keep playing.

222
00:18:56,589 --> 00:18:57,960
Yeah, what’s up, Fah?

223
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,145
What’s up?

224
00:19:02,709 --> 00:19:03,894
That's my line.

225
00:19:04,247 --> 00:19:05,367
You’re the one who called.

226
00:19:06,896 --> 00:19:07,586
Uh...

227
00:19:08,474 --> 00:19:09,111
Fah.

228
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,511
Can I ask you something?

229
00:19:12,429 --> 00:19:13,047
What?

230
00:19:13,674 --> 00:19:14,336
I mean...

231
00:19:14,776 --> 00:19:16,060
When you liked your boyfriend,

232
00:19:16,651 --> 00:19:17,782
how did you know?

233
00:19:23,373 --> 00:19:23,871
Thit.

234
00:19:24,481 --> 00:19:25,008
Yeah?

235
00:19:26,364 --> 00:19:27,709
That’s a weird question.

236
00:19:28,828 --> 00:19:30,699
Just answer me.

237
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:34,235
I just liked him.

238
00:19:35,082 --> 00:19:35,860
He was cute.

239
00:19:37,284 --> 00:19:38,517
I wanted to be with him.

240
00:19:40,222 --> 00:19:41,260
Something like that.

241
00:19:42,444 --> 00:19:43,404
That’s it?

242
00:19:43,977 --> 00:19:45,628
You thought he was cute and wanted to be with him?

243
00:19:46,939 --> 00:19:49,263
What does “cute” even mean?

244
00:19:50,402 --> 00:19:52,066
I’ve never felt that before.

245
00:19:53,284 --> 00:19:53,914
Wait.

246
00:19:54,647 --> 00:19:56,235
Is this about you?

247
00:19:56,992 --> 00:19:57,583
Huh?

248
00:19:58,965 --> 00:20:00,152
Do you like someone?

249
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:02,281
Do I look that obvious?

250
00:20:02,794 --> 00:20:03,240
Well...

251
00:20:04,925 --> 00:20:05,869
You seem restless.

252
00:20:09,558 --> 00:20:10,226
Or...

253
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:12,989
Do you like Dao?

254
00:20:20,266 --> 00:20:21,841
No, Fah. You’re crazy.

255
00:20:22,807 --> 00:20:24,573
I said no.

256
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:26,622
Shit, why would I like—

257
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,500
How long have you been standing there?

258
00:20:33,257 --> 00:20:33,992
Just now.

259
00:20:38,514 --> 00:20:39,145
You little—

260
00:20:39,853 --> 00:20:40,811
Were you eavesdropping?

261
00:20:43,448 --> 00:20:44,660
I was coming to the toilet.

262
00:20:52,056 --> 00:20:53,414
Alright, I’ll call you later.

263
00:21:06,573 --> 00:21:09,696
That reaction means I’m right, doesn’t it?

264
00:21:10,877 --> 00:21:11,733
I don’t like him.

265
00:21:14,674 --> 00:21:16,197
Are you crazy? I don’t like him.

266
00:21:16,592 --> 00:21:17,034
Really?

267
00:21:17,875 --> 00:21:19,188
Then why did you call?

268
00:21:21,194 --> 00:21:21,825
Damn.

269
00:21:23,835 --> 00:21:24,377
But...

270
00:21:24,927 --> 00:21:25,654
Fah.

271
00:21:26,382 --> 00:21:27,628
I just...

272
00:21:27,982 --> 00:21:28,600
You what?

273
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:31,114
I just...

274
00:21:32,509 --> 00:21:33,570
I...

275
00:21:34,450 --> 00:21:36,047
Fuck.

276
00:21:36,792 --> 00:21:37,792
You never thought

277
00:21:37,922 --> 00:21:39,339
you’d be someone who could like another person, right?

278
00:21:40,459 --> 00:21:41,831
You know me too well.

279
00:21:42,226 --> 00:21:44,149
Are you living in my head or what?

280
00:21:44,737 --> 00:21:45,445
Damn.

281
00:21:46,275 --> 00:21:47,065
Honestly?

282
00:21:47,659 --> 00:21:48,429
I don’t think it’s strange.

283
00:21:49,558 --> 00:21:51,817
Love always seemed so far from you.

284
00:21:52,045 --> 00:21:53,032
You know,

285
00:21:53,438 --> 00:21:55,125
I never thought there’d be a day

286
00:21:55,407 --> 00:21:57,308
you’d ask me about this.

287
00:21:57,554 --> 00:21:58,801
Isn’t it weird, Fah?

288
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:00,349
I mean...

289
00:22:00,844 --> 00:22:02,374
It doesn’t feel possible.

290
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:05,251
I’ve never cared about this stuff before.

291
00:22:06,231 --> 00:22:07,360
Yeah.

292
00:22:07,986 --> 00:22:11,425
But from what I see, he’s actually pretty interesting.

293
00:22:12,004 --> 00:22:13,614
He suits you.

294
00:22:13,928 --> 00:22:15,365
Not too much.

295
00:22:15,665 --> 00:22:16,691
Not too little.

296
00:22:17,080 --> 00:22:18,637
If you miss this one,

297
00:22:18,986 --> 00:22:20,893
you won’t find another like him.

298
00:22:22,314 --> 00:22:23,471
I don’t know, Fah.

299
00:22:24,299 --> 00:22:26,989
I don’t even know how to act.

300
00:22:28,551 --> 00:22:29,979
This is me, Fah.

301
00:22:30,928 --> 00:22:32,917
Me. A guy like me.

302
00:22:33,173 --> 00:22:34,111
Shit.

303
00:22:34,808 --> 00:22:35,515
Alright.

304
00:22:35,994 --> 00:22:37,920
I’ve got a simple question for you.

305
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:41,534
Between having him and not having,

306
00:22:42,131 --> 00:22:43,660
which do you prefer?

307
00:22:47,465 --> 00:22:48,245
You.

308
00:22:50,685 --> 00:22:52,195
Why does it have to be you, huh?

309
00:22:53,202 --> 00:22:53,893
What?

310
00:23:00,386 --> 00:23:01,019
Hey.

311
00:23:02,069 --> 00:23:02,632
Yea?

312
00:23:04,044 --> 00:23:05,032
Your mom’s pictures.

313
00:23:14,851 --> 00:23:15,322
Hey.

314
00:23:17,598 --> 00:23:18,607
Did you draw all of these?

315
00:23:20,048 --> 00:23:22,253
Some of them were almost finished by your mom.

316
00:23:22,954 --> 00:23:24,496
I just added a few details.

317
00:23:28,882 --> 00:23:29,597
Wait.

318
00:23:31,328 --> 00:23:33,102
You’re with me all the time.

319
00:23:33,645 --> 00:23:34,917
When did you even draw these?

320
00:23:36,493 --> 00:23:38,195
Late at night. I couldn’t sleep.

321
00:23:38,819 --> 00:23:40,100
So I found something to do.

322
00:23:49,125 --> 00:23:52,477
I studied what your mom drew and tried to copy it.

323
00:23:54,457 --> 00:23:55,703
It might not look the same.

324
00:24:04,611 --> 00:24:05,614
Do you like it?

325
00:24:15,943 --> 00:24:16,576
Yeah.

326
00:24:22,124 --> 00:24:22,545
Uh...

327
00:24:26,013 --> 00:24:28,071
Yeah, I like it.

328
00:24:28,736 --> 00:24:29,561
It’s really nice.

329
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,678
Mm.

330
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,508
I’ll take a picture and show Direk.

331
00:24:36,761 --> 00:24:37,340
Okay.

332
00:25:20,912 --> 00:25:22,607
What’s wrong with you?

333
00:25:22,632 --> 00:25:25,331
Is it pretty? Do you like it?
Direk, do you like it? It’s cute, right?

334
00:25:27,709 --> 00:25:28,333
(Blocked)

335
00:25:33,614 --> 00:25:35,352
What did you do to get blocked by your dad again?

336
00:25:36,967 --> 00:25:39,885
I just texted him saying I missed him, that’s all.

337
00:25:40,456 --> 00:25:41,176
That’s it?

338
00:25:41,277 --> 00:25:42,622
Why the hell would he block you?

339
00:25:44,903 --> 00:25:45,848
I don’t know.

340
00:25:46,487 --> 00:25:48,380
Go tell him to unblock me.

341
00:25:49,537 --> 00:25:50,712
You make it hard for me every time.

342
00:25:52,114 --> 00:25:53,204
Alright.

343
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,533
That’s it. I’m heading back.

344
00:25:56,570 --> 00:25:57,565
Why’d you rush back anyway?

345
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:59,900
Thailand’s doing better without you here.

346
00:26:02,751 --> 00:26:03,989
I was afraid you’d miss me.

347
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:05,475
Pfft.

348
00:26:08,245 --> 00:26:09,419
Yeah, that’s it.

349
00:26:26,211 --> 00:26:27,638
Are you upset about something?

350
00:26:28,349 --> 00:26:28,844
Hey.

351
00:26:29,677 --> 00:26:31,025
That’s kind of a tough question.

352
00:26:36,834 --> 00:26:38,170
I just saw you staring.

353
00:26:40,862 --> 00:26:41,758
I was just looking.

354
00:26:43,117 --> 00:26:44,355
You’re sitting right in front of me.

355
00:26:46,484 --> 00:26:47,582
What else am I supposed to look at?

356
00:26:59,791 --> 00:27:01,783
You’re pretty good to lean on, you know.

357
00:27:11,991 --> 00:27:13,238
What do you mean?

358
00:27:16,290 --> 00:27:17,426
I don’t know either.

359
00:28:35,411 --> 00:28:36,694
Are you going to pick up Khun John?

360
00:28:39,441 --> 00:28:41,155
Maew said he’d be back late.

361
00:28:42,121 --> 00:28:44,278
So I thought I’d go back and sleep first.

362
00:28:48,057 --> 00:28:49,084
Hey, are you sick or something?

363
00:28:58,254 --> 00:28:59,745
You look tired.

364
00:29:01,432 --> 00:29:02,725
Just tired from traveling.

365
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:30,961
Thit

366
00:29:31,650 --> 00:29:32,669
No, man.

367
00:29:33,607 --> 00:29:35,090
No way.

368
00:29:57,754 --> 00:29:59,085
You think I’d like someone like that?

369
00:30:01,177 --> 00:30:02,142
No way.

370
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,213
Oh.

371
00:30:09,466 --> 00:30:10,152
Thit.

372
00:30:10,660 --> 00:30:11,093
Hm?

373
00:30:12,124 --> 00:30:13,717
- Yeah.
- You’re back?

374
00:30:14,568 --> 00:30:15,200
Hey.

375
00:30:16,589 --> 00:30:19,149
I was gone for a bit. What happened to you?

376
00:30:24,188 --> 00:30:25,192
Hey, hey.

377
00:30:26,161 --> 00:30:27,885
Damn.

378
00:30:29,426 --> 00:30:30,379
Wait.

379
00:30:31,422 --> 00:30:32,586
Shit.

380
00:30:33,755 --> 00:30:35,502
Did Do really break up with you?

381
00:30:40,863 --> 00:30:41,706
Yeah.

382
00:30:47,105 --> 00:30:47,952
Why?

383
00:30:50,674 --> 00:30:53,447
They say the more you contact spirits,

384
00:30:55,130 --> 00:30:57,520
the easier it is for them to reach you.

385
00:31:02,934 --> 00:31:03,611
What?

386
00:31:06,546 --> 00:31:09,551
Lately, other spirits have been approaching me too.

387
00:31:10,752 --> 00:31:12,669
One of them even hurt me.

388
00:31:14,949 --> 00:31:17,887
And you know, I’m not that strong mentally.

389
00:31:19,244 --> 00:31:20,602
The only solution is

390
00:31:22,174 --> 00:31:24,506
I have to stop dealing with spirits altogether.

391
00:31:28,302 --> 00:31:29,573
Oh.

392
00:31:30,965 --> 00:31:32,620
So Do broke up with you.

393
00:31:33,491 --> 00:31:34,161
Yeah.

394
00:31:40,148 --> 00:31:40,922
Hey.

395
00:31:41,342 --> 00:31:41,842
Hm?

396
00:31:42,485 --> 00:31:43,967
I told him I was okay.

397
00:31:45,072 --> 00:31:46,154
I was okay.

398
00:31:47,968 --> 00:31:49,865
He just disappeared.

399
00:31:51,748 --> 00:31:53,176
He won’t come even if I call.

400
00:31:54,641 --> 00:31:56,154
Do you get it?

401
00:31:59,459 --> 00:32:00,717
I miss him.

402
00:32:09,242 --> 00:32:11,755
No matter what, she’s not here anymore.

403
00:32:12,743 --> 00:32:15,100
It’s the ones who are still alive

404
00:32:15,422 --> 00:32:17,383
who deserve to be happy the most.

405
00:32:18,682 --> 00:32:20,602
If you keep being this sad,

406
00:32:22,311 --> 00:32:24,511
how can your mom be happy?

407
00:32:27,940 --> 00:32:29,936
I can’t do this, man.

408
00:32:32,503 --> 00:32:34,002
Damn it, Meen.

409
00:32:37,062 --> 00:32:38,610
Shit.

410
00:32:39,865 --> 00:32:42,125
Why the hell did you come back so I can see you?

411
00:32:44,223 --> 00:32:45,948
Yeah, I know.

412
00:32:47,066 --> 00:32:49,579
Do would want you to be happy for sure.

413
00:32:51,662 --> 00:32:52,620
Don’t cry.

414
00:32:54,832 --> 00:32:56,469
He’d rather see you smile.

415
00:33:08,075 --> 00:33:09,931
- What the hell is this?
- Who are you?

416
00:33:10,094 --> 00:33:10,617
You jerk.

417
00:33:11,456 --> 00:33:12,607
That hurts, asshole.

418
00:33:12,708 --> 00:33:14,454
Get out of my friend’s body right now.

419
00:33:14,601 --> 00:33:15,225
Meen.

420
00:33:17,677 --> 00:33:20,149
I’ve never heard you talk like that before.

421
00:33:22,238 --> 00:33:23,151
Who are you?

422
00:33:24,857 --> 00:33:26,588
I just heard it from someone else.

423
00:33:29,282 --> 00:33:32,779
It’s just a simple word that helped me.

424
00:33:34,681 --> 00:33:36,832
I hope it can help you too, Meen.

425
00:33:48,785 --> 00:33:49,728
I’ll smile.

426
00:33:50,720 --> 00:33:52,459
I really will.

427
00:33:56,241 --> 00:33:57,780
I’ll be happy for him too.

428
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:03,511
- Yeah.
- But give me some time, okay?

429
00:34:10,383 --> 00:34:12,591
Yeah, I get it.

430
00:34:13,269 --> 00:34:14,971
Stuff like this takes time.

431
00:34:22,779 --> 00:34:23,608
Hey, Meen.

432
00:34:24,312 --> 00:34:25,645
- Huh?
- Can I ask you something?

433
00:34:26,315 --> 00:34:26,997
What?

434
00:34:31,182 --> 00:34:33,038
When Do passed away,

435
00:34:34,813 --> 00:34:35,970
you were really hurt, right?

436
00:34:39,967 --> 00:34:41,044
Look at my face.

437
00:34:42,374 --> 00:34:44,610
Of course I was. I cried like this.

438
00:34:46,982 --> 00:34:48,232
And...

439
00:34:48,986 --> 00:34:50,302
have you ever thought

440
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:53,361
that if it would end like this,

441
00:34:55,663 --> 00:34:57,260
maybe it was better not to start?

442
00:35:01,133 --> 00:35:03,167
Even if I knew he would die,

443
00:35:05,222 --> 00:35:07,302
or if I had a time machine to go back,

444
00:35:08,281 --> 00:35:09,251
I’d still choose him.

445
00:35:11,337 --> 00:35:12,577
Why?

446
00:35:14,610 --> 00:35:15,951
If it never started,

447
00:35:16,654 --> 00:35:17,758
it wouldn’t hurt.

448
00:35:18,508 --> 00:35:21,320
Doesn’t that mean one day it has to disappear anyway?

449
00:35:31,121 --> 00:35:31,951
I don’t know.

450
00:35:34,031 --> 00:35:35,013
All I know is,

451
00:35:36,677 --> 00:35:37,952
without him,

452
00:35:39,174 --> 00:35:40,977
I wouldn’t have made it through each day.

453
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:46,671
You know,

454
00:35:47,954 --> 00:35:49,354
all these past years,

455
00:35:51,528 --> 00:35:53,656
I never regretted being with him.

456
00:35:56,428 --> 00:35:57,663
I’m even thankful to myself

457
00:35:58,191 --> 00:35:59,053
for choosing him.

458
00:36:04,700 --> 00:36:05,522
From now on,

459
00:36:07,337 --> 00:36:08,897
even if he’s not here anymore,

460
00:36:12,288 --> 00:36:14,361
those memories still make me happy.

461
00:36:23,994 --> 00:36:24,555
Why...

462
00:36:25,642 --> 00:36:27,205
are you asking me this?

463
00:36:35,736 --> 00:36:36,988
A friend of mine

464
00:36:38,077 --> 00:36:40,078
really likes someone.

465
00:36:43,244 --> 00:36:44,958
He’s never liked anyone before,

466
00:36:46,534 --> 00:36:48,029
but this one is different.

467
00:36:51,075 --> 00:36:52,380
Once he fell for them,

468
00:36:53,373 --> 00:36:55,877
he wanted to spend his whole life with them.

469
00:36:59,722 --> 00:37:02,161
But he’s scared that one day, if that person disappears,

470
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:06,691
he won’t be able to handle it.

471
00:37:11,942 --> 00:37:12,909
Your friend?

472
00:37:14,117 --> 00:37:15,296
Yeah, my friend.

473
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:30,297
It’s not strange if he’s scared.

474
00:37:32,588 --> 00:37:34,207
How much does he like that person?

475
00:37:36,028 --> 00:37:37,681
Does he want them in his every day?

476
00:37:41,928 --> 00:37:44,328
Or if he woke up tomorrow and they were gone,

477
00:37:44,576 --> 00:37:45,497
would he be okay?

478
00:37:46,573 --> 00:37:47,712
Try to imagine it.

479
00:37:49,195 --> 00:37:50,568
If they suddenly disappeared,

480
00:37:52,757 --> 00:37:53,730
would that be better?

481
00:38:00,743 --> 00:38:01,514
I think

482
00:38:02,642 --> 00:38:04,835
I’m not the only one who’s got it bad.

483
00:38:07,912 --> 00:38:08,725
What are you talking about?

484
00:38:09,257 --> 00:38:10,659
I told you, it’s about my friend.

485
00:38:13,351 --> 00:38:15,325
Idiot, you’re so obvious.

486
00:38:16,158 --> 00:38:18,106
Even a dog could tell.

487
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:21,608
Bottoms up.

488
00:38:29,324 --> 00:38:30,565
Are you in love?

489
00:38:32,894 --> 00:38:34,405
My friend is.

490
00:38:35,477 --> 00:38:37,988
I don’t buy this love stuff. It’s nonsense.

491
00:38:38,284 --> 00:38:39,040
Oh really?

492
00:39:09,131 --> 00:39:09,801
Sorry.

493
00:39:12,450 --> 00:39:13,291
Did I wake you up?

494
00:39:16,102 --> 00:39:17,177
Are you leaving?

495
00:39:18,281 --> 00:39:19,168
You already knew, didn’t you?

496
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,773
Thank you for everything, Daotok.

497
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:24,754
Yeah.

498
00:39:26,699 --> 00:39:27,834
Please take care of Meen.

499
00:40:05,991 --> 00:40:08,211
P’Fah and I will take John back to your room.

500
00:40:08,444 --> 00:40:09,872
We don’t want you driving late at night.

501
00:40:15,065 --> 00:40:16,398
Thanks, Maew.

502
00:40:16,957 --> 00:40:17,880
No problem at all.

503
00:40:18,204 --> 00:40:19,121
You’re back already?

504
00:40:21,890 --> 00:40:23,124
Yeah, I’m back.

505
00:40:23,557 --> 00:40:24,674
Dao’s back.

506
00:40:25,613 --> 00:40:27,484
We missed you so much, Dao.

507
00:40:28,355 --> 00:40:29,985
Heh, not me.

508
00:40:30,728 --> 00:40:32,540
You’re the one who kept talking about him.

509
00:40:44,229 --> 00:40:44,654
Oh?

510
00:40:50,182 --> 00:40:50,798
You drink?

511
00:41:00,739 --> 00:41:01,343
Whoa.

512
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:02,967
That’s strong.

513
00:41:06,368 --> 00:41:06,912
Want some?

514
00:41:07,411 --> 00:41:08,380
Nah, I’m driving.

515
00:41:10,242 --> 00:41:11,558
You two, seriously.

516
00:41:11,785 --> 00:41:13,364
The second you hear “bar,”

517
00:41:13,487 --> 00:41:14,611
you come running.

518
00:41:15,730 --> 00:41:16,280
Damn.

519
00:41:16,745 --> 00:41:19,397
Hey, didn’t you say you came with a friend? Where are they?

520
00:41:20,681 --> 00:41:21,638
I’m heading out first.

521
00:41:21,666 --> 00:41:22,364
There.

522
00:41:23,611 --> 00:41:25,942
- I’m leaving first.
- Meen, that’s enough, damn it.

523
00:41:26,391 --> 00:41:27,690
How much are you gonna drink?

524
00:41:28,503 --> 00:41:31,084
- Hi there!
- Go grab your own drink.

525
00:41:31,225 --> 00:41:32,420
Cheers.

526
00:41:33,014 --> 00:41:33,474
Hey.

527
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:36,650
You don’t even know each other and you’re already clinking glasses?

528
00:41:37,099 --> 00:41:38,251
Nice one.

529
00:41:38,391 --> 00:41:41,001
It’s more fun with a crowd like this.

530
00:41:41,619 --> 00:41:43,120
Coming with just you

531
00:41:43,404 --> 00:41:44,757
is boring as hell.

532
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:46,851
True. Want me to invite more people?

533
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,869
Sure.

534
00:41:49,317 --> 00:41:52,657
- Go ahead.
- I’ll call Dao. Haven’t seen him in a while. Miss him like crazy.

535
00:41:53,082 --> 00:41:54,534
Hey, no need to call him, North.

536
00:41:55,625 --> 00:41:56,213
Why not?

537
00:41:59,407 --> 00:42:00,822
Seriously, don’t call him.

538
00:42:02,517 --> 00:42:03,373
I want to.

539
00:42:03,952 --> 00:42:06,025
Damn it, I said don’t call him, North.

540
00:42:07,357 --> 00:42:08,374
Why are you so pissed?

541
00:42:09,081 --> 00:42:10,407
Did you two fight or something?

542
00:42:12,589 --> 00:42:13,245
No.

543
00:42:15,254 --> 00:42:16,417
Then why can’t I call him?

544
00:42:16,888 --> 00:42:20,133
Come on, if he gets drunk I’ll take care of him.
I can carry him.

545
00:42:20,231 --> 00:42:21,608
- I said don’t call him, North.
- Hey!

546
00:42:24,825 --> 00:42:26,051
What the hell is your problem?

547
00:42:27,795 --> 00:42:29,583
You must really hate my friend.

548
00:42:29,925 --> 00:42:30,940
What did he ever do to you?

549
00:42:31,594 --> 00:42:32,202
Yeah.

550
00:42:32,792 --> 00:42:33,856
What did he do?

551
00:42:35,832 --> 00:42:37,860
Someone like him wouldn’t hurt you.

552
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:39,770
He’s quiet,

553
00:42:40,075 --> 00:42:41,007
and he’s a good guy.

554
00:42:41,325 --> 00:42:43,222
Not a jerk like you.

555
00:42:43,539 --> 00:42:45,391
He went to San Fran to help you.

556
00:42:45,746 --> 00:42:46,856
Do you really hate him?

557
00:42:47,435 --> 00:42:49,336
You don’t even know how to be grateful.

558
00:42:49,577 --> 00:42:51,755
- You're not that great.
- Yeah, right.

559
00:42:52,029 --> 00:42:55,410
Damn, he went all the way to San Fran for you.

560
00:42:56,269 --> 00:42:56,674
Shit.

561
00:42:57,509 --> 00:42:58,087
Wait.

562
00:42:59,548 --> 00:43:00,428
Hey,

563
00:43:00,777 --> 00:43:02,084
are you talking about Dao?

564
00:43:03,502 --> 00:43:04,800
You know Dao too?

565
00:43:04,905 --> 00:43:06,405
Well—

566
00:43:06,844 --> 00:43:09,429
He’s my benefactor.

567
00:43:10,499 --> 00:43:14,136
He helped me see my late boyfriend.

568
00:43:14,423 --> 00:43:14,931
Hey—

569
00:43:15,755 --> 00:43:16,659
Don’t tell me

570
00:43:17,281 --> 00:43:18,131
your boyfriend is…

571
00:43:18,970 --> 00:43:21,228
- The wall-scratching ghost.
- Yeah.

572
00:43:22,370 --> 00:43:23,457
Holy shit.

573
00:43:24,247 --> 00:43:25,770
Just talking about it makes me sad.

574
00:43:54,030 --> 00:43:55,211
Didn’t you say you quit smoking?

575
00:43:56,625 --> 00:43:57,905
It’s fine once in a while. North won’t mind.

576
00:43:59,917 --> 00:44:00,708
Jo.

577
00:44:03,345 --> 00:44:03,914
Yeah?

578
00:44:05,684 --> 00:44:07,054
Have you ever felt like this?

579
00:44:08,419 --> 00:44:10,638
Trying to get something out of your head

580
00:44:11,432 --> 00:44:12,617
but you just can’t?

581
00:44:15,228 --> 00:44:15,800
Yeah.

582
00:44:17,970 --> 00:44:18,711
When?

583
00:44:27,727 --> 00:44:29,324
When I tried to get over North.

584
00:44:33,717 --> 00:44:34,748
So what did you do?

585
00:44:37,367 --> 00:44:38,207
Nothing.

586
00:44:39,177 --> 00:44:40,225
I just couldn’t.

587
00:44:42,205 --> 00:44:44,241
But one day, you might lose him.

588
00:44:45,934 --> 00:44:47,447
Will you be able to handle that?

589
00:44:49,866 --> 00:44:50,531
No.

590
00:44:53,053 --> 00:44:54,942
But if I didn’t have North,

591
00:44:56,259 --> 00:44:57,262
I wouldn’t handle that either.

592
00:44:59,275 --> 00:45:00,371
It might hurt even more.

593
00:45:05,521 --> 00:45:06,681
Why, Jo?

594
00:45:07,675 --> 00:45:09,998
Wouldn’t it be better if it never started?

595
00:45:12,105 --> 00:45:12,862
You really think that?

596
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,598
Ask yourself.

597
00:45:20,001 --> 00:45:21,336
Why should I?

598
00:45:25,435 --> 00:45:26,961
So… who is it?

599
00:45:28,128 --> 00:45:29,010
The one you came with?

600
00:45:34,930 --> 00:45:36,731
Damn it.

601
00:45:37,047 --> 00:45:37,880
Shit.

602
00:45:42,570 --> 00:45:44,226
So it finally happened to you.

603
00:45:46,469 --> 00:45:47,448
Yeah, damn.

604
00:45:48,091 --> 00:45:49,779
I can’t believe this shit actually happened to me.

605
00:45:50,471 --> 00:45:52,085
It’s so fucking messed up, you know?

606
00:45:53,946 --> 00:45:55,032
Maybe it’s not that bad.

607
00:45:56,598 --> 00:45:57,536
It is, damn it.

608
00:45:58,792 --> 00:46:00,527
I still feel like shit right now.

609
00:46:01,951 --> 00:46:02,794
Jo.

610
00:46:03,475 --> 00:46:05,063
I never wanted to cross that line.

611
00:46:05,988 --> 00:46:06,607
Arthit.

612
00:46:07,681 --> 00:46:09,130
You already crossed it.

613
00:46:10,219 --> 00:46:11,493
Otherwise you wouldn’t be overthinking like this.

614
00:46:15,654 --> 00:46:16,336
You know what?

615
00:46:17,937 --> 00:46:19,810
This shit’s so damn complicated.

616
00:46:20,432 --> 00:46:21,586
These messed-up feelings.

617
00:46:23,251 --> 00:46:24,961
I don’t even know how to act, Jo.

618
00:46:27,331 --> 00:46:29,140
I’ve never felt anything like this before.

619
00:46:30,820 --> 00:46:31,951
So what are you gonna do?

620
00:46:35,706 --> 00:46:36,398
I don’t know.

621
00:46:39,484 --> 00:46:40,802
Maybe I’ll try stepping back first.

622
00:46:42,149 --> 00:46:42,863
I mean…

623
00:46:43,327 --> 00:46:45,656
Maybe I just caught feelings ’cause we’re always together.

624
00:46:48,980 --> 00:46:51,490
When I tried to move on from North, I thought the same as you.

625
00:46:53,429 --> 00:46:55,604
That once I let go, everything would get easier.

626
00:46:57,890 --> 00:46:59,632
When I really tried to move on,

627
00:46:59,988 --> 00:47:00,875
I was just like you.

628
00:47:02,195 --> 00:47:03,480
Drinking every day.

629
00:47:04,060 --> 00:47:05,041
Talking nonsense all day.

630
00:47:07,665 --> 00:47:08,595
Shit.

631
00:47:10,601 --> 00:47:13,164
I don’t wanna end up stuck in a loop like you, asshole.

632
00:47:14,275 --> 00:47:15,768
Maybe you won’t.

633
00:47:19,715 --> 00:47:20,868
If you can really move on.

634
00:47:25,088 --> 00:47:26,020
I can.

635
00:47:27,293 --> 00:47:28,345
Yeah, I can, damn it.

636
00:47:28,571 --> 00:47:29,805
I can handle it.

637
00:47:31,659 --> 00:47:34,035
But if one day you realize you can’t step back,

638
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:36,063
then move forward right away.

639
00:47:36,328 --> 00:47:37,598
Before it’s too late.

640
00:47:38,761 --> 00:47:40,671
If someone like you falls for him,

641
00:47:41,579 --> 00:47:42,447
maybe others stand a chance too.

642
00:48:03,801 --> 00:48:05,494
Chug it. Come on, chug.

643
00:48:08,497 --> 00:48:09,192
Arthit.

644
00:48:10,028 --> 00:48:11,379
What the hell’s wrong with you?

645
00:48:12,545 --> 00:48:14,980
I asked you to come cheer me up ’cause my boyfriend dumped me.

646
00:48:15,928 --> 00:48:17,979
Why do you look worse than I do?

647
00:48:19,648 --> 00:48:20,522
I need to get drunk.

648
00:48:21,531 --> 00:48:23,280
So I can finally stop to think about this shit.

649
00:48:24,422 --> 00:48:24,995
Hey.

650
00:48:25,225 --> 00:48:26,522
What did you two go talk about?

651
00:48:26,674 --> 00:48:27,989
Why’d he come back like this?

652
00:48:28,651 --> 00:48:29,702
That guard dog.

653
00:48:30,127 --> 00:48:31,948
Turned into a jealous dog.

654
00:48:32,462 --> 00:48:34,077
Jealous of what the hell?

655
00:48:34,765 --> 00:48:36,767
I’m not jealous of anything.

656
00:48:38,365 --> 00:48:39,007
Good.

657
00:48:39,920 --> 00:48:41,942
Then you’d better get over him fast before someone else claims him.

658
00:48:43,315 --> 00:48:45,294
Because once that happens,

659
00:48:45,842 --> 00:48:47,355
you might not even have the right to look at him.

660
00:48:50,490 --> 00:48:52,137
I won’t even have the right to look?

661
00:48:53,278 --> 00:48:54,062
Shit.

662
00:48:55,002 --> 00:48:56,988
He’s my favorite view, damn it.

663
00:48:57,105 --> 00:48:58,080
Yours?

664
00:48:59,062 --> 00:48:59,696
Yeah.

665
00:49:01,137 --> 00:49:02,620
Looking at him makes me feel good.

666
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:06,776
No one else enjoys the view like I do.

667
00:49:07,450 --> 00:49:08,231
You sure about that?

668
00:49:14,103 --> 00:49:14,654
North.

669
00:49:14,948 --> 00:49:15,604
Yeah?

670
00:49:15,672 --> 00:49:17,435
I heard your friend from Engineering

671
00:49:17,635 --> 00:49:18,801
likes that kid a lot.

672
00:49:20,038 --> 00:49:21,060
Which kid?

673
00:49:22,263 --> 00:49:23,051
Daotok.

674
00:49:26,450 --> 00:49:27,305
Shit.

675
00:49:28,579 --> 00:49:29,505
What?

676
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:33,158
Why does it have to be my friend?

677
00:49:35,005 --> 00:49:36,583
I’d like to know that too.

678
00:49:37,288 --> 00:49:38,653
Why your friend?

679
00:49:40,819 --> 00:49:42,014
What do you even like about him?

680
00:49:43,238 --> 00:49:44,851
I’m telling you, don’t get your hopes up.

681
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:46,880
You’ve got no chance.

682
00:49:47,462 --> 00:49:51,217
Yeah, I know, asshole. I’m trying, okay?

683
00:49:52,696 --> 00:49:53,731
First love?

684
00:50:02,195 --> 00:50:02,877
Yeah.

685
00:50:05,860 --> 00:50:06,982
Honestly,

686
00:50:08,822 --> 00:50:11,201
if you liked someone else,

687
00:50:11,571 --> 00:50:13,703
I’d help you all the way.

688
00:50:15,111 --> 00:50:16,980
But this is my friend.

689
00:50:18,388 --> 00:50:20,760
I want my friend to meet someone good.

690
00:50:21,219 --> 00:50:22,878
Damn it.

691
00:50:26,154 --> 00:50:28,040
- Hey, North.
- Huh?

692
00:50:28,623 --> 00:50:29,998
Which friend of yours?

693
00:50:30,148 --> 00:50:31,524
The one who likes him.

694
00:50:32,697 --> 00:50:34,324
A lot of them.

695
00:50:34,577 --> 00:50:36,949
Daotok’s super popular.

696
00:50:37,410 --> 00:50:39,717
- Guys ask for his Line every day.
- And what did you do?

697
00:50:39,936 --> 00:50:42,386
- I just gave it to them.
- Just like that?

698
00:50:42,856 --> 00:50:45,090
Why the hell would you give it out?

699
00:50:45,847 --> 00:50:47,088
Engineering guys?

700
00:50:47,951 --> 00:50:49,871
Besides their gear, what’s so great about them?

701
00:50:50,499 --> 00:50:52,620
Hey, that’s not fair, P’Arthit.

702
00:50:53,459 --> 00:50:54,745
I’m in Engineering too.

703
00:50:55,241 --> 00:50:57,225
Oh come on, I’m in Engineering.

704
00:50:59,204 --> 00:51:00,105
Don’t worry, Arthit.

705
00:51:01,890 --> 00:51:03,496
Everyone in this world is better than you.

706
00:51:03,890 --> 00:51:05,302
Damn it, Jo. Asshole.

707
00:51:13,291 --> 00:51:14,576
You bastard, Arthit.

708
00:51:14,768 --> 00:51:17,100
You’re freaking pathetic.

709
00:51:17,656 --> 00:51:20,592
Look at me — I’m walking straight as hell.

710
00:51:22,798 --> 00:51:24,917
Hey, are we at the room yet?

711
00:51:25,340 --> 00:51:27,801
Thanks for walking me back, man.

712
00:51:30,394 --> 00:51:32,691
- Are we there yet?
- Your keycard?

713
00:51:32,700 --> 00:51:34,019
- Huh?
- Your keycard.

714
00:51:34,411 --> 00:51:35,194
Your keycard.

715
00:51:37,595 --> 00:51:39,368
It should be in my pants.

716
00:51:42,161 --> 00:51:44,702
- Somewhere in your pants?
- Where exactly?

717
00:51:44,875 --> 00:51:46,302
In my pants.

718
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:47,591
I don’t see it.

719
00:51:47,644 --> 00:51:48,586
What about this?

720
00:51:49,136 --> 00:51:51,120
That’s not it, idiot.

721
00:51:52,294 --> 00:51:55,152
Shit. Damn it.

722
00:51:55,681 --> 00:51:58,234
I lost my keycard again.

723
00:52:01,091 --> 00:52:02,499
What should we do, P’Jo?

724
00:52:20,733 --> 00:52:22,118
Daotok.

725
00:52:30,066 --> 00:52:30,980
Can you help us out?

726
00:52:31,863 --> 00:52:33,967
P’Arthit freaking lost his keycard.

727
00:52:44,117 --> 00:52:44,776
Please?

728
00:52:46,322 --> 00:52:47,100
Mm.

729
00:52:47,574 --> 00:52:48,315
Fine.

730
00:52:52,051 --> 00:52:52,660
Nice.

731
00:52:54,416 --> 00:52:55,213
Ugh.

732
00:53:02,142 --> 00:53:04,604
Can I take the bed?

733
00:53:04,822 --> 00:53:05,804
Stop being picky.

734
00:54:24,589 --> 00:54:25,752
Hey.

735
00:54:29,866 --> 00:54:31,256
Dao.

736
00:54:32,448 --> 00:54:33,488
What?

737
00:54:34,717 --> 00:54:37,533
Engineering guys only have that gear thing going for them.

738
00:54:37,928 --> 00:54:39,537
If you’re gonna choose,

739
00:54:40,979 --> 00:54:42,914
pick a med student instead.

740
00:54:44,841 --> 00:54:45,842
Trust me.

741
00:54:48,069 --> 00:54:51,774
Hey, can you hear me?

742
00:54:54,195 --> 00:54:55,265
Hey.

743
00:55:25,654 --> 00:55:27,197
You’re sleeping so comfortably.

744
00:55:28,029 --> 00:55:30,053
Leaving me freezing to death on the floor.

745
00:56:42,152 --> 00:56:42,623
Hey.

746
00:58:20,365 --> 00:58:22,847
Wow, sleeping in his room makes you that happy?

747
00:58:26,881 --> 00:58:27,656
What are you talking about?

748
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:29,383
You’re not really over him, are you?

749
00:58:30,546 --> 00:58:32,336
I’m serious, Jo.

750
00:58:36,437 --> 00:58:39,080
Since when does someone serious go cuddle the person they’re trying to forget?

751
00:58:39,976 --> 00:58:40,478
Huh?

752
00:58:42,917 --> 00:58:43,841
How did you even know?

753
00:58:45,122 --> 00:58:45,930
I guessed.

754
00:58:48,020 --> 00:58:49,560
Are you serious?

755
00:58:51,696 --> 00:58:53,318
You guessed right.

756
00:58:54,327 --> 00:58:55,311
Oh?

757
00:58:55,842 --> 00:58:56,971
You’ve done it before, haven’t you?

758
00:58:58,933 --> 00:59:01,822
North and I were dating. What’s weird about that?

759
00:59:03,005 --> 00:59:04,411
Then what are you to him?

760
00:59:05,294 --> 00:59:06,152
His brother?

761
00:59:09,422 --> 00:59:10,942
He wasn’t feeling well.

762
00:59:11,237 --> 00:59:12,925
It was cold, so I hugged him.

763
00:59:13,891 --> 00:59:14,823
Oh.

764
00:59:15,287 --> 00:59:16,348
I see.

765
00:59:17,133 --> 00:59:18,072
Jo, you asshole.

766
00:59:18,834 --> 00:59:19,343
Damn it.

767
00:59:19,762 --> 00:59:20,678
You never stop teasing me.

768
00:59:22,271 --> 00:59:22,894
Seriously.

769
00:59:23,880 --> 00:59:24,665
I’m not teasing you.

770
00:59:25,481 --> 00:59:26,620
Hill once said

771
00:59:27,277 --> 00:59:29,364
don’t approach someone with half-hearted feelings.

772
00:59:30,440 --> 00:59:32,180
If you like him or not, be clear about it.

773
00:59:32,608 --> 00:59:34,884
Right now your actions and your words

774
00:59:35,514 --> 00:59:37,075
don’t match at all.

775
00:59:37,463 --> 00:59:38,361
Honestly, Arthit,

776
00:59:39,471 --> 00:59:40,568
you already know that.

777
00:59:41,770 --> 00:59:42,675
Yeah.

778
00:59:45,042 --> 00:59:46,663
Did you tell Tonfah yet?

779
00:59:46,819 --> 00:59:47,688
About moving on?

780
00:59:48,352 --> 00:59:50,247
Not yet.

781
00:59:50,954 --> 00:59:51,805
Are you still going to tell him?

782
00:59:52,520 --> 00:59:53,500
Maybe you don’t have to.

783
00:59:54,885 --> 00:59:55,718
Jo.

784
00:59:56,185 --> 00:59:57,576
But this time I’m serious.

785
00:59:58,343 --> 01:00:00,020
I’m really going to move on.

786
01:00:00,893 --> 01:00:03,047
Besides cuddling, what else did you do?

787
01:00:04,783 --> 01:00:05,694
You tell me.

788
01:00:06,223 --> 01:00:06,914
Did you sleep together?

789
01:00:07,567 --> 01:00:08,896
What the hell, Jo?

790
01:00:09,186 --> 01:00:10,804
Come on, it's possible if it were you.

791
01:00:11,162 --> 01:00:13,543
- What kind of person do you think I am?
- A jerk.

792
01:00:17,760 --> 01:00:18,330
Well...

793
01:00:20,773 --> 01:00:22,293
He wasn’t feeling well.

794
01:00:23,080 --> 01:00:24,019
I was scared he might die.

795
01:00:24,805 --> 01:00:25,983
So I

796
01:00:27,721 --> 01:00:29,060
took care of him a little.

797
01:00:29,922 --> 01:00:32,408
I just didn’t want another ghost next door, that’s all.

798
01:00:33,552 --> 01:00:35,487
I didn’t know this is how people “move on.”

799
01:00:36,222 --> 01:00:36,711
See?

800
01:00:37,392 --> 01:00:39,494
I tell you everything and you still tease me like this.

801
01:00:39,610 --> 01:00:40,908
You’re contradicting yourself.

802
01:00:46,706 --> 01:00:48,591
These things take time, don’t they?

803
01:00:49,841 --> 01:00:52,783
Whatever. Take your whole life if you want.

804
01:00:54,521 --> 01:00:55,668
Yeah, I know.

805
01:00:56,539 --> 01:00:57,881
I'm not gonna use my whole life or anything.

806
01:01:00,534 --> 01:01:01,093
I guess.

807
01:01:05,928 --> 01:01:07,730
Hello, Khun Phuangthong.

808
01:01:08,582 --> 01:01:10,242
I think a ghost is messing with me.

809
01:01:11,160 --> 01:01:12,047
A ghost in your room?

810
01:01:12,866 --> 01:01:13,545
Who did it?

811
01:01:14,097 --> 01:01:15,185
What did it do to you?

812
01:01:15,856 --> 01:01:18,162
I don’t know who did it.

813
01:01:18,690 --> 01:01:19,734
It felt suffocating.

814
01:01:20,918 --> 01:01:21,946
Like I was being hugged.

815
01:01:23,272 --> 01:01:24,502
That’s really scary.

816
01:01:25,019 --> 01:01:26,875
Did you do something to them?

817
01:01:28,065 --> 01:01:29,131
No.

818
01:01:29,788 --> 01:01:31,752
I haven’t even been in the room for days.

819
01:01:31,985 --> 01:01:34,425
We’ve always been fine before.

820
01:01:35,177 --> 01:01:37,671
Or maybe they’re upset we didn’t make merit for them.

821
01:01:38,133 --> 01:01:40,389
Alright, I’ll make merit for them.

822
01:01:40,777 --> 01:01:42,764
I’m going to the temple anyway.

823
01:01:43,413 --> 01:01:44,152
Mm.

824
01:01:44,854 --> 01:01:46,831
Please do it for me, Khun Phuangthong.

825
01:01:48,035 --> 01:01:48,687
Mm.

826
01:01:49,320 --> 01:01:50,765
Tell me if anything happens.

827
01:01:51,328 --> 01:01:52,802
Take care of yourself.

828
01:01:54,078 --> 01:01:55,460
Yes, Khun Phuangthong.

829
01:01:56,077 --> 01:01:58,186
Today is my first day of the semester.

830
01:01:58,542 --> 01:02:00,644
Could you give me a blessing?

831
01:02:01,102 --> 01:02:02,177
Good luck, dear.

832
01:02:02,610 --> 01:02:04,237
I hope you encounter only good things.

833
01:02:04,721 --> 01:02:07,388
May today be a good day for you.

834
01:02:07,758 --> 01:02:08,645
Thank you.

835
01:02:13,007 --> 01:02:14,802
That’s all for now, Khun Phuangthong.

836
01:02:26,085 --> 01:02:26,791
Going to class?

837
01:02:27,582 --> 01:02:28,158
Yeah.

838
01:02:29,920 --> 01:02:30,748
Well,

839
01:02:31,367 --> 01:02:32,337
Feeling better from cold?

840
01:02:34,080 --> 01:02:36,260
Thanks for wiping me down.

841
01:02:38,842 --> 01:02:39,431
Yeah.

842
01:02:41,974 --> 01:02:43,050
How are you getting there?

843
01:02:44,317 --> 01:02:45,165
By motorcycle?

844
01:02:55,232 --> 01:02:55,767
Wait.

845
01:02:57,277 --> 01:02:58,202
Uh—

846
01:02:59,108 --> 01:03:00,044
I’ll take you.

847
01:03:00,934 --> 01:03:03,651
You just recovered. You shouldn’t be riding.

848
01:03:05,400 --> 01:03:06,192
It’s fine.

849
01:03:07,561 --> 01:03:08,250
I’ll take you.

850
01:03:58,048 --> 01:03:59,280
Hey, where do you study again?

851
01:04:00,254 --> 01:04:01,622
Faculty of Science.

852
01:04:02,420 --> 01:04:03,577
What did you say?

853
01:04:04,801 --> 01:04:05,697
Science.

854
01:04:09,885 --> 01:04:11,502
Say it louder.

855
01:04:16,019 --> 01:04:16,902
Science.

856
01:04:19,774 --> 01:04:20,318
Yeah.

857
01:04:52,361 --> 01:04:54,071
You’re hugging me tight. Scared?

858
01:04:54,591 --> 01:04:55,525
A little.

859
01:04:56,280 --> 01:04:57,402
I don’t usually ride on the back of a motorcycle.

860
01:04:58,002 --> 01:04:58,462
Oh?

861
01:05:00,822 --> 01:05:01,515
Mm.

862
01:05:20,096 --> 01:05:20,955
Thanks.

863
01:05:24,770 --> 01:05:25,703
What time do you finish?

864
01:05:26,845 --> 01:05:27,440
5 p.m.

865
01:05:28,982 --> 01:05:29,912
Then you come to wait here.

866
01:05:31,773 --> 01:05:32,506
You’re picking me up?

867
01:05:33,585 --> 01:05:36,284
I brought you here. How else would you get back?

868
01:05:37,722 --> 01:05:39,749
- I can walk.
- Are you kidding?

869
01:05:40,693 --> 01:05:41,600
I’ll wait here.

870
01:05:46,297 --> 01:05:47,459
Thanks for the ride.

871
01:05:51,733 --> 01:05:52,774
Say it like you mean it.

872
01:05:56,244 --> 01:05:57,475
I do mean it.

873
01:05:59,072 --> 01:06:00,736
"Thank you," properly.

874
01:06:03,768 --> 01:06:04,345
Say it.

875
01:06:07,466 --> 01:06:08,410
Thank you.

876
01:06:10,091 --> 01:06:11,613
Say my name too.

877
01:06:13,457 --> 01:06:15,254
Thank you for the ride.

878
01:06:16,958 --> 01:06:17,588
P’Arthit.

879
01:06:40,992 --> 01:06:42,248
I like someone already.

880
01:06:42,365 --> 01:06:44,560
- I’m trying to court him.
- It won’t be easy, P’.

881
01:06:44,684 --> 01:06:46,133
If you’re trying to court him,

882
01:06:46,333 --> 01:06:47,571
what’s so hard about it?

883
01:06:47,780 --> 01:06:50,265
Just be myself. Be sincere. Be natural.

884
01:06:50,616 --> 01:06:52,081
I’ll break down the door for real.

885
01:06:53,194 --> 01:06:56,657
Maybe don’t be yourself.
Just be a little better, that’s enough.

886
01:06:56,823 --> 01:06:59,665
Since I started courting you, how many points have I earned?

887
01:06:59,721 --> 01:07:00,589
Zero.

888
01:07:00,899 --> 01:07:02,078
Why do you like me?

889
01:07:02,277 --> 01:07:03,866
That’s a question I don’t know either.

890
01:07:03,921 --> 01:07:05,182
I just know it has to be you.

891
01:07:05,552 --> 01:07:07,408
Well, zero—from having nothing at all.

892
01:07:08,305 --> 01:07:10,250
From now on, I’m starting to count.
